{
  "texts": [
    "In the event of a class imbalance issue, it is a more precise measurement.",
    "False positive rate and TPR are helpful metrics for evaluating a model's effectiveness at detecting NTLs, but they do not account for precision.",
    "Hence, PR-AUC is a helpful metric that is also an appropriate measure for imbalanced datasets to assess the model's precision.",
    "Thus, the mathematical form for the precision, recall, F1-score, and MCC are given in Eqs 8-11 (Razavi et al., 2019).",
    "In contrast to performance measures, to assess the significance of the differences in the prediction performance of the proposed models, the Diebold and Mariano Test (DMT) was performed (Meidan et al., 2020)."
  ]
}